      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Monks in my opinion, &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Masters of Endurance, (dmg over time)&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Great Feats of physical and mental strength (impressive DPS, and survivability)&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;~A monk is not a hulking rippling mass of muscle, he is a focus, disciplined warrior, who knows what to attack and when, how to dmg something with the least amount of effort, to strike and move with Speed unparrelelled leaving a mob wondering how many times it was just hit, only to realise to late that it was fatal. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I love being a monk because&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I only die if i am not paying attention, or FD wants me dead.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I can provide impressive dps to a group.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;In most places even Rss/Nest i do not require heals if i play smart, saving cleric mana.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I love a monks survivability&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I LOVE pulling, because i get to ensure a group gets the mobs it can handle, and if you do you job right people will always remember you for more groups, a smart player is one that is remembered. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;A monk if played smart, tanks just fine. however would love more shielding on items&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Avoidance is $ cap is easy to obtain with 1/2 our items coated in it.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Working with other monks pulling for raid that require team work.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I can safely say looking at what we have been getting so far and the hard work our monk corespondent does for us and the open ear he recieves, makes me glad to play a monk. You guys know who you are, so from a monk to another Thanks Brother!&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</description>
