    <item>
      <title>Re: Discuss Class Re-Envisionment</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&amp;message.id=10304#M10304</link>
      <description>Monks&lt;br&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Monks are pullers primarily, and also contribute to fights as great off-tanks and pure melee DPS. Our primary role is to pull mobs to the group or raid, by using our many skills such as spliting, lulling and feigning death. Once we get the required amount of mobs, we can bring them to the group for the main tank to use their defensive abilities on, while we off-tank any additional mob until another tank can get them, or a mezer can mez them. Once that is done we share high DPS alongside other melees, but never being able to get as much DPS as classes who's primary goal is to dish out damage, such as rogues and bersekers. We're at the crossroad of offense and defense, and our disciplines and skills include tools to do both, from pulling, survival and increased offense.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;This is my definition of a monk, what it was when I started it, what it is now and what it will always be and the way I play my character.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
