    <item>
      <title>Re: Discuss Class Re-Envisionment</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&amp;message.id=9699#M9699</link>
      <description>A bard is vastly superior to monk with regards to pulling.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;One if you have not noticed high end content mob almost have superior run speed to everyone except a bard.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;  a) If you have had to pull in anguish raid, bards fly around out running everything. While monks have to take a beating (even with new run aa). So you pull use crippling strike, mend, potions, and/or earthwalk/dreamwalk. In contrast, bard will agro out run , get to camp and fade. If a bard gets in trouble instant fade (mana), DA song and even seen snare song used. Consequently, it is rare a bard takes a hit or 2 during the pull. When I pull anguish our guild expects 2 or even 3 trash mobs in camp at the same time. 1300hitters x3 on your back the whole time. I am not talking a short distance either.&lt;br&gt;  ---Advantage BARDS&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;  b) Lets turn to places like QVIC.&lt;br&gt;    Once again run speed is a huge advantage. A monk pulls using alot of the same tactics as points a, just taking less damage than anguish. However it reasonable to use FD or ID to get a good split. Lulls work ok. (Remember 65 lull is pacify, reaction radius modifer vs 69lull is just a reaction radius modifer (oversite ?) Lulls are usefull in situation where you do not path a mob too close to another. Certainly, there are few more perks for monk in these areas. Turning to bards, they run up agro and 30 sec later a mob gets to camp. Almost the same a monk just far far quicker. Lets turn to splitting, while a monk has to use FD and smarts, a bard can lull, mez (heavily useful), Divine Aura (DA), snare (rarely used), fade (mana)and even agro a mob thru walls to get warps. &lt;br&gt;Example Common Bard strat: A bard runs up does the DA runs in agros a ton of mob (all between Mnet etc), keeps close enough to get all of them (lazy agro mobs). Once everything is pretty much outside of the temple and on him/her run a large circle thru the zone. Speeding up on the end and then Fades almost to Mnet. Then agros selos outside warps it (cheap bard agro BS)  thru the wall then runs back to camp with mnet before 90 pct of the mobs have pathed back. However, if they missed a mob just mez continue and fade to lose agro once at camp. Sounds simple enough does it not. &lt;br&gt;Example 2 (monks): A monk can do the tradition pull 2 by 2 to camp til you get to Mnet and hopefully beat respawn (varaible quality of players killing in camp (non raid cleric death= slow down), knowing the area (taking a short cut or 2, or/and cannot die during the pull process. Old fashion pull and kill method. Second idea is a make off of bard strat listed above. You use the same method however you can run and get as many as you can ( use voidance, earthwalk). Then you keep 15 to 18 mobs together without dying (cause your disc went bye bye). Go into to dreamwalk speed hopefully get them far enough away with 18 sec disc or is 12 sec anyways...Do the great circle as explained above get back to MNET (disc is gone bye bye far before you get there) ID (Imitate Death) clear all agro ..Agro Mnet get it outside with normal run speed before a boat load of mobs get back. Run Mnet to camp and if add comes camp has to deal with ( remember FD during this phase = Mnet warps home). Certainly somewhat doable however it takes alot more skill , and heck of lot more luck. Cannot screw up cause all discs will take 15 to 30 plus mins to recoil.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Comparing the 2 classes: Huge advantage to bards cause of 1) Time saver to raid (esp in the past if racing guilds) 2)Those little perks of speed mez lull fade da etc etc are huge huge advantage if used properly 3)Bards use some agro thru wall trick. Certainly weighing it all together it far far easier as a bard. &lt;br&gt; ---ADVANTAGE BARDS&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Other raid areas: Certainly there are some advantages in certain situation where a fd split in tight quarters is great advantage than bard fade. So without listing a huge list of raid strats, I will call this situational pulling. All in All it weighs out equal between the 2 classes. Advantage generally greater where Selos is enabled to the bard and where it is not then monk pokes slightly ahead. Certainly, I have a 'bag of tricks' that I use when I can to yield a small perk. Sadly, most take camping or fair amount of time to recover cause they are expendable. \&#xD;&lt;br&gt;Again NO ADVANTAGE TO EITHER.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;So what can you take from this. First comment, new run speed AA would be better served if we were in the area of 80pct run speed (10 pct increase per aa). Certainly, not in the range of selos but it means that we are not totally covered in whelts on our back, once we get to camp. Secondly, Lull and Fade = Phanton series and FD (ID)...so thats a fair balance in pulling. However again turning to the perks, not even in the same ballpark. Mez'n, DA'n, etc is not even a balanced to what a monk can do. Sure you can say we have better DPS. However, most highend guilds do not consider monks good DPS in situations where DPS on one thing and killing add trash (you will find us on trash).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Sorry I did not clean up this post, I have to run =( (but not run too fast=) )</description>
