&lt;P&gt;Mingo_Djinn wrote:&lt;BR&gt;There seems here to be an lot of people mentioning how much better bards are at pulling than monks, how bards have all these fun abilities, how as monks they just sit about waiting on the bard to pull.... &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;**SMURF**???&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Ok, so bards get innate skills to allow them to mez / lull / run fast / fade etc...&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Get a grip.... I've played a monk for near on 6 years, I pull for my guild on raids constantly and I pull for groups all the time as well.....are bards better pullers than me?? Hell NO! Effective as bards can be and as quick as bards can be with their innate abilities to split mobs etc, I've never found this to be a problem for a monk.&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;It would all depend on the person behind the bard.&amp;nbsp; Just like not all monks are great expert pullers neither are all bards, it is just much easier for a non puller bard to pull just as well as a puller monk.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Maybe if you feel that you can't pull anywhere near as well or as fast as a bard, you shouldn't be a monk in the first place.&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Well, as I stated above not all monks play them to pull or even with the intention of pulling.&amp;nbsp; This would be just like them telling you that if you can't dps as well as a rogue or berzerker then you shouldn't be a monk.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Just how can a bard pull "faster" than a monk when as a mob is dying you're bringing another back to camp??&lt;BR&gt;There are no differences in speed here.... chain pulling negates that.&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Unfortunately do to the fact that the bard can run significantly faster than a monk can, they can pull faster.&amp;nbsp; Chain pulling has 0 effect on that.&amp;nbsp; It just means that the monk does considerably less dps.&amp;nbsp; The monk will have to leave camp sooner to get the next mob than a bard would have to so the bard's utility is active for the whole group longer than the monks dps would be on the mob.&amp;nbsp; Also by pulling faster there is also the fact that when a monk has to split mobs it can take a fair amount of time for a monk to split them that it would not take a bard of equal skill, or less skill at times.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Ok, so a bard may often be able to split mobs faster than a monk, so initially breaking a spawn may be slightly quicker if a bard is doing it... but there are also instances where monks can split mobs faster than bards...&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Then by all means share these places with everyone.&amp;nbsp; I can't really think of anything that isn't a raid target where on average a bard couldn't pull it as fast or faster than a monk.&amp;nbsp; I am sure there are places where it is true, and I'm also sure that the monks more skilled at pulling can probably pull faster than many bards.&amp;nbsp; But in the same way most bards can pull faster than many monks.&amp;nbsp; Skill and experience in pulling are needed on the monk's part, but not always necessary on the bard's.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
It's all about how you play your class and how well you understand your own abilities...&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Stop bitching about how much better bards are at pulling than monks, go learn something about your class and how to pull!!&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It's not a matter of people not understanding their class.&amp;nbsp; Until recently monks weren't even officially considered a pulling class, though they did acknowledge that we were used for it.&amp;nbsp; The bard however has always been and still is officially considered to be a primary if not the primary pulling class, thus why they have all the tools.&amp;nbsp; Anything that a monk can go learn about their class and pulling there is a&amp;nbsp;bard that can go and learn about their class and pulling.&amp;nbsp; Then in the content that is actively used by most people the bard with equal knowledge about theirown class and how to pull will 9 times out of 10 pull as well or faster than a monk who knows just as much about the monk class and pulling.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Besides in 99% of today's content run speed = pulling speed.&amp;nbsp; The bards just have a much faster way to get rid of their adds.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
