      <title>Re: Discuss Class Re-Envisionment</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&amp;message.id=8700#M8700</link>
      <description>I have one simple request that I really need before I can discuss re-envisionment of the monk class (or any other class).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Can you please share what the developer's model of where they want the monk to end up? Describe (in general scope, not specific detail) how they foresee (after all the changes are done) monks in the lineup.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In years gone by, we had mission statement of varying degrees of detail. Things like:&lt;br&gt;We (EQ developers) want warrior damage to be the baseline. Rogue damage to be 1.4, monk to be 1.3, etc etc etc. (I'm sure they're not these numbers, years ago it ceased being accurate or meaningful).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We've had a more recent statement about order of 'tankability', warrior better than knight better than monk better than (etc etc), as the design template for luclin-&gt;Pop.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Can you give us your 'plan'? How can we discuss reevisionment talking into a vacuum? If we're given what you want the end point to be, we can collaborate and assist you in reaching that goal (either by ideas that could accomplish it, or pointing out where things that've been attempted have fallen short or overshot the mark).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Roles and issues that seem to directly affect desirability:&lt;br&gt;DPS&lt;br&gt;'taking damage' (distinct from tanking, since tanking also involves aggro control to keep the thing from changing targets)&lt;br&gt;tanking&lt;br&gt;pulling&lt;br&gt;at-range roles (for encounters where being in melee range is nominal suicide for people 'other than tank(s)'.)&lt;br&gt;healing&lt;br&gt;slowing&lt;br&gt;crowd control&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I've probably missed a few. But I guess I'm looking to see how you think monks should fit in the grander scheme of things (relative to other classes), and obviously there are going to be things monks excel at (dps, hopefully) and are lousy at (healing, one presumes). I'd also expect the roles to be weighed with both xp groups AND raiding in mind, but that may be hoping for too much.&lt;br&gt;But we can't have meaningful dialog about how to reach a goal, when the goal is wrapped in sackcloth, locked in a chest, and stored in a pitch-black bank vault.</description>
